50|$|The modern law of unjust {{enrichment}} encompasses {{what was once}} known as the law of quasi-contract. Its precise scope remains a matter of controversy. Beyond quasi-contract, it is sometimes said to encompass the law relating to subrogation, contribution, <b>recoupment,</b> and claims to the traceable substitutes of misapplied property.|$|E
